rk. Nafzger said there was a concern that Street Sense wouldn't have time to get properly prepared for the Travers if he ran the 1.5-mile Belmont. The horse will be able to rest and compete in one or two races between now and the Travers, including possibly the Jim Dandy. "I know there's disappointment we're not going to the Belmont," Nafzger said. "But somewhere we want to make another stand." Major 35W detour this weekend Turnabout at the lake: Fish goes boying New catalog offers XL in everything from toilet seats to lawn chairs Man found dead on railroad tracks in Wisconsin Fugitive sex offender sought St. Paul teacher arrested; sex with student alleged Patrick Reusse: Twins are rewarded for faith in Guerrier Turnabout at the lake: Fish goes boying Major 35W detour this weekend Oops! Check for millions misdirected to woman NWA to flex new financial muscle Floor of Convention Center needs a $3 million foot-lift New catalog offers XL in everything from toilet seats to lawn chairs Adult kids can collect for suffering when parents die, Wisconsin court says BORDER COLLIE PUPS ABCA. Work or pet, rsd with kids, very loved, 3M/2F, shts,... 243 similar items on Star Tribune. All rights reserved. Star Tribune Company Store Company Directory & Contacts Newspaper Subscriptions & Service 425 Portland Av. S., Minneapolis, MN 55488 (612) 673-4000
