http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/15-1&fd=R&url=http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/scorecard/othernews.asp%3FarticleID%3D203448&cid=1116848841&ei=j_1eRoSRLouUrgO3usjSDQ Seattle Post-Intelligencer: Other Sports Skip ads and navigation Thursday, May 31, 2007 RSL adds veteran Kotschau Salt Lake City, UT (Sports Network) - Real Salt Lake added veteran MLS defender Ritchie Kotschau on Wednesday. Kotschau has played in 224 games - starting 202 - for the Chicago Fire, Tampa Bay Mutiny, Colorado Rapids and Columbus Crew. He won an MLS Cup title in 1998 with the expansion Fire. He started 23 of 26 games for Columbus last year, contributing one goal and two assists. He has 10 goals and 17 assists in his career. Kotschau was awarded to Real after clearing waivers Tuesday, months after being picked by Toronto FC in the expansion draft. "Ritchie is a player that brings us a great deal of depth defensively," RSL Technical Director John Ellinger said. "He's a very, very smart soccer player - there are few, if any, situations he has not been in. He's comfortable on the ball in the back and should mesh well with the personalities on our squad. We're glad to have him in the fold." Real (0-3-5) returns to action Saturday at New England. Economy nearly stalled in first quarter N.H. governor signs civil unions law Iraq residents rise up against al-Qaida Putin: U.S. has triggered new arms race Five cos. win gov't telecom contract Listener helps save ailing disc jockey Wal-Mart cashier: I was fired for joking Promotional fax mistaken for bomb threat Musician canned for focus on wrong organ Couple sue Wal-Mart over slip in vomit New breed of cat retails for $22,000 Dying vet planned a final mission 'Spam King' suspect seized Recent grads offer real-world perspective to Class of 2007 Pre-Draft Notebook: Halperin says 'no' to Sonics Microsoft Surface brings computing to the table Ancestry.com puts 90M war records online New breed of cat retails for $22,000 Where car thieves love to tread