http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/16i-0&fd=R&url=http://www.theonlinewire.com/articleView.aspx%3FID%3D2731&cid=1116754239&ei=j_1eRoSRLouUrgO3usjSDQ Garrett Atkins three-run home run gets Rockies past Royals List All Sportsbooks (Text Only) Garrett Atkins three-run home run gets Rockies past Royals Garrett Atkins hit a three-run home run and Taylor Buchholz tossed seven strong innings to lead the Colorado Rockies past Kansas City Royals, 6-4. Buchholz (2-2) scattered five hits and gave up just one unearned run while striking out four and walking two for the Rockies, who had lost four of five. Ryan Shealy's two-out, three-run homer in the top of the ninth brought the Royals within two runs, but Brian Fuentes entered the game and got Esteban German to groundout for his 11th save of the season. Brad Hawpe hit a two-run home run for Colorado, while Todd Helton also went deep and scored three runs. Shealy finished 3-for-4 for Kansas City, which saw its three-game winning streak come to an end. Royals ace Gil Meche (3-2) gave up his first runs on the road this season, yielding eight hits and five runs through five-plus innings of work in the loss. A first inning error by center fielder Willy Taveras allowed Mark Grudzielanek to score on Mark Teahen's single. However, with one on and two outs in the fourth, Hawpe's fourth home run of the season put Colorado in front. Matt Holliday then led off the sixth with a double, Helton walked and Atkins followed with a blast over the right-field wall to make it 5-1 in favor of the Rockies. Helton added a two-out, solo homer in the seventh for a five-run Colorado advantage. Game Notes This was Meche's first-ever appearance against the Rockies...Before the game, Colorado designated infielder John Mabry for assignment and recalled outfielder Ryan Spilboroughs from Triple-A Colorado Springs. Place your MLB picks and discuss baseball handicapping at , a great place for people to share info, opinions, and for wanna be touts to show