ploded. Hewitt broke in the first and fifth games of the decider and took the match with a love service game after 3hrs 28min on Court Philippe Chatrier when Gaudio hit a lazy, tired forehand long. Hewitt had to come back from two sets down to beat Michael Russell in the first round of this year&#39;s Australian Open. His first such dramatic recovery came against Guillermo Canas in the fourth round here in 2001, and the second was in 2003 when he beat Roger Federer in a Davis Cup semi-final. News24 is now available on your cellphone. -- Top stories in this category -- Merciless Nadal storms on Hewitt stages stunning comeback Sharapova romps to victory French flops stun Parisian fans
