ll try to bounce back against Marlins starter Web Obermueller (1-3, 5.02 ERA), who is getting the ball on three days' rest. The right-hander was moved up in the rotation because Sergio Mitre is still nursing a hamstring injury. In his last start, Obermueller allowed three runs and six hits while striking out five in seven innings as Florida lost 4-3 to Milwaukee on Thursday night. He has never had less than four days of rest in between starts in his major league career. ''I'm excited to go,'' Obermueller said. ''In the past, I've pitched like that in relief and went like three innings and went a couple of days later for a spot start. This will be the quickest turnaround, going seven innings and then going four days later.'' Obermueller was with Milwaukee when he made his only career appearance against the Braves, surrendering seven runs and seven hits in 4 1-3 innings in a 7-1 loss on Aug. 7, 2003. Florida lost three of four in Milwaukee after winning its previous six games on the road. The Marlins lost the finale of their series with the Brewers 3-0 on Sunday, getting shut out for the third time this season. The Marlins lead the season series with the Braves 3-2, splitting two games in a rain-shortened series in Atlanta from April 13-15. The teams will make up a game as part of a doubleheader Tuesday. Newspaper Home Delivery - Subscribe Today Privacy Policy/Your California Privacy Right Add USATODAY.com RSS feeds
